<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 14:32:30 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>通过不完整的测量设置对纠缠进行实用且高效的验证</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/practical-and-efficient-verification-of-entanglement-with-incomplete-measurement-settings</link><description>当只有一组有限或次优的测量可通过实验获得时，一种新方法可以验证量子态是否纠缠，从而提供了一种在现实场景中验证纠缠的有效方法。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/practical-and-efficient-verification-of-entanglement-with-incomplete-measurement-settings2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 14:32:29 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/practical-and-efficient-verification-of-entanglement-with-incomplete-measurement-settings</guid></item><item><title>年龄似乎不会增加妊娠期心血管风险</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/age-does-not-appear-to-drive-cardiovascular-risk-in-pregnancy</link><description>威尔康奈尔医学的最新研究表明，潜在的心血管风险（而不是年龄较大）会导致妊娠期间出现静脉血栓栓塞、心肌病和心力衰竭等并发症。这些发现可能会鼓励医生在患者怀孕前更积极地解决患者的心血管健康问题。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/age-does-not-appear-to-drive-cardiovascular-risk-in-pregnancy2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 14:17:29 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/age-does-not-appear-to-drive-cardiovascular-risk-in-pregnancy</guid></item><item><title>从噪音中收集信息</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/gleaning-information-from-noise</link><description>研究人员得出了一个通用极限，将噪声与远离平衡的系统中的扰动响应联系起来。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/gleaning-information-from-noise.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 14:02:29 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/gleaning-information-from-noise</guid></item><item><title>超快开关器件为人工智能硬件解锁低功耗光电转换</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/ultrafast-switching-device-unlocks-low-power-optical-to-electrical-conversion-for-ai-hardware</link><description>随着人工智能和物联网等技术变得越来越普遍，现代能源需求正在飙升，研究人员一直在努力开发能够跟上的硬件。现在，东京大学的一组研究人员开发了一种超快且节能的非易失性开关器件，在一篇文章中进行了描述&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/ultrafast-switching-device-unlocks-low-power-optical-to-electrical-conversion-for-ai-hardware2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 13:47:29 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/ultrafast-switching-device-unlocks-low-power-optical-to-electrical-conversion-for-ai-hardware</guid></item><item><title>通过恢复关键代谢成分来为老化肌肉干细胞充电的新方法</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/a-new-way-to-recharge-aging-muscle-stem-cells-by-restoring-a-key-metabolic-component</link><description>失去肌肉力量是衰老的自然组成部分。这种下降的核心是肌肉干细胞（MuSC）数量的减少，肌肉干细胞是负责在我们一生中维持和再生肌肉组织的特殊细胞。肌肉力量的丧失会严重影响活动能力，增加跌倒、骨折的风险，最重要的是，会增加失去独立性的风险。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/a-new-way-to-recharge-aging-muscle-stem-cells-by-restoring-a-key-metabolic-component2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 13:32:29 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/a-new-way-to-recharge-aging-muscle-stem-cells-by-restoring-a-key-metabolic-component</guid></item><item><title>写在眼睛上：视网膜的生物年龄如何帮助预测骨质疏松症风险</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/written-in-the-eye-how-the-retinas-biological-age-could-help-predict-osteoporosis-risk</link><description>眼睛是帮助我们可视化外部世界的高分辨率生物设备，现在被用作评估我们内部健康的门户。科学家发现，更仔细地评估一个人的视网膜如何老化可以提供有关骨骼健康的重要提示，特别是在骨质疏松症等情况下，骨质疏松症会使骨骼变得更脆弱，更容易骨折。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/written-in-the-eye-how-the-retinas-biological-age-could-help-predict-osteoporosis-risk2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 13:17:29 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/written-in-the-eye-how-the-retinas-biological-age-could-help-predict-osteoporosis-risk</guid></item><item><title>扭曲的 WSe2 揭示了难以捉摸的电荷中性量子模式</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/twisted-wse%e2%82%82-reveals-elusive-charge-neutral-quantum-modes</link><description>量子材料，即具有受量子力学定律影响的特性的材料，在过去的几十年中引起了广泛的关注。它们独特的性能使这些材料有利于众多尖端技术的开发，包括量子计算机、高灵敏度传感器和节能电子产品。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/twisted-wsee28282-reveals-elusive-charge-neutral-quantum-modes2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 13:02:29 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/twisted-wse%e2%82%82-reveals-elusive-charge-neutral-quantum-modes</guid></item><item><title>生物工程师将蛋白质工程和测试浓缩到一天</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/bioengineers-condense-protein-engineering-and-testing-to-a-single-day</link><description>蛋白质对于生命和工业至关重要。有无数的蛋白质可以被改造来治疗甚至治愈严重的疾病和细胞功能障碍。工业应用同样前景广阔，蛋白质越来越多地用作食品制造和消费洗涤剂中的酶。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/bioengineers-condense-protein-engineering-and-testing-to-a-single-day2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 12:47:29 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/bioengineers-condense-protein-engineering-and-testing-to-a-single-day</guid></item><item><title>黑暗的月球陨石坑可以容纳用于月球导航的超稳定激光器</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/dark-lunar-craters-could-host-ultrastable-lasers-for-moon-navigation</link><description>它们是太阳系中最黑暗、最寒冷的地方之一：数百个月球陨石坑，其中许多位于月球南极，从未接受阳光直射，永远处于阴影之中。这正是为什么物理学家 Jun Ye 和他的同事认为这些陨石坑是建造超稳定激光器关键部件的完美场所。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/dark-lunar-craters-could-host-ultrastable-lasers-for-moon-navigation2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 12:32:29 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/dark-lunar-craters-could-host-ultrastable-lasers-for-moon-navigation</guid></item><item><title>学习物理可能会让一些学生脱轨：新研究表明让他们走上正轨的最佳方法</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/learning-physics-can-derail-some-students-new-research-shows-the-best-way-to-keep-them-on-track</link><description>对于许多本科生来说，第一次探索物理学的复杂性，从涉足高等数学到在大型讲座中吸收信息，可能是一项艰巨的任务—— &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/learning-physics-can-derail-some-students-new-research-shows-the-best-way-to-keep-them-on-track2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Tue, 19 May 2026 12:17:29 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/learning-physics-can-derail-some-students-new-research-shows-the-best-way-to-keep-them-on-track</guid></item></channel></rss>